                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00114 Pacific War/231: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-06">July 6,
                            1943</date>.<lb/>[Received July 6—9:29 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3975. American interests Japan. Department’s 1255, May 25. Legation Tokyo
                    telegraphs: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Japanese Foreign Office replied Japanese Government assumes cost
                            maintenance American POWs, internees and in general assists indigent
                            citizens enemy countries. Each time Swiss representative desires give
                            supplementary relief should request authorization Japanese Government
                            which will make decision after examining if relief corresponds necessity
                            and if possible transmit funds persons concerned.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
